    <edge id="e0" source="Light" target="PHYB">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">Red light activates phytochrome B photoreceptor; Pfr form accumulates in light.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1104/pp.113.2.611</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">ma3 sorghum lacks a 123-KD phytochrome that predominates in light-grown plants and that is present in non-ma3 plants.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e1" source="Light" target="PHYC">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">Phytochrome C is activated by red light; Ma5 locus encodes SbPhyC.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1038/s41598-023-42306-8</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">Ma5 = SbPhyC (Sobic.001G087100, Chr01)</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e2" source="Light" target="CCA1">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">Dawn light entrains the morning oscillator: CCA1 expression peaks at dawn and is light-gated. Conservation across Arabidopsis and grasses (rice OsCCA1).</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1186/1471-2229-12-32</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">LHY, CCA1, TOC1 (circadian oscillator)...entrained by light-dark cycles.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e3" source="Light" target="LHY">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">Dawn light activates LHY morning expression alongside CCA1 in the core oscillator. Light entrainment is a canonical clock input.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1186/1471-2229-12-32</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">LHY, CCA1, TOC1 (circadian oscillator)...entrained by light-dark cycles.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e4" source="Blue_Light" target="FKF1">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">SbFKF1/SbFFL contains a LOV domain that forms a covalent adduct with FMN upon blue-light illumination, activating the F-box protein to recruit substrates via SCF ubiquitin ligase.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1002/pld3.281</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">SbGI physically interacts with the sorghum FKF1-like (SbFFL) protein, and the SbGI-SbFFL interaction is stimulated by blue light.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e5" source="Photoperiod_LD" target="PRR37">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">Long-day light evening phase coincides with SbPRR37 evening mRNA peak via PhyB; in SD the evening peak is eliminated because the phase occurs in darkness.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1073/pnas.1106212108</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">peaks of SbPRR37 mRNA abundance in the morning and in the evening...evening peak of SbPRR37 expression in SD does not occur due to darkness.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e6" source="Photoperiod_LD" target="GHD7">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">LD induces evening peak of SbGhd7 via PhyB; SD eliminates this peak (darkness).</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1371/journal.pone.0105352</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">evening peak of expression is attenuated in SD when this phase occurs in darkness.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e7" source="PHYB" target="PRR37">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">PhyB (Ma3) is required for evening-light activation of SbPRR37 in long days; loss of PhyB eliminates the evening expression peak of SbPRR37.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1371/journal.pone.0105352</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">PhyB is required for light activation of SbPRR37 and SbGHD7 expression in the evening of long days.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e8" source="PHYB" target="GHD7">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">PhyB activates SbGhd7 expression through evening-phase light signaling in long days.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1371/journal.pone.0105352</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">Sorghum phytochrome B inhibits flowering in long days by activating expression of SbPRR37 and SbGHD7, repressors of SbEHD1, SbCN8 and SbCN12.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e9" source="PHYB" target="FT1">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">PhyB represses SbCN15 (SbFT1 = Hd3a-subclade florigen) via a mechanism that is PRR37/Ghd7-independent and photoperiod-independent. Loss of PhyB causes ~60-fold upregulation of SbCN15.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1371/journal.pone.0105352</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">PhyB mediated repression of SbCN15 expression occurs regardless of photoperiod.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e10" source="PHYB" target="CO">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">PhyB/PhyC mediate SbCO protein destabilisation in LD daylight hours, reducing CO activity (opposite of Arabidopsis); in SD this is released.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1186/1471-2229-14-148</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">Reduced PhyB/C-mediated degradation of SbCO in SD, relative to LD.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e11" source="PHYB" target="ELF3">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">PhyB inactivates ELF3 post-translationally; in rice, OsPhyB inactivates OsELF3 through post-translational modifications in response to light, thereby attenuating Evening Complex repression on Ghd7/PRR37 in LD.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1073/pnas.2122582119</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">OsPhyB inactivates OsELF3 through post-translational modifications in response to light.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e12" source="PHYC" target="PRR37">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">Phytochrome C (Ma5) acts together with PhyB to delay flowering in LD through activation of floral repressors; PhyC-light signaling contributes to PRR37 activation.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1080/15592324.2016.1261232</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">Ma5 encodes phytochrome C (phyC)...acts as a photoperiod-dependent flowering repressor.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e13" source="PHYC" target="GHD7">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">PhyC contributes to evening-light signaling that activates Ghd7 in LD, parallel to PhyB.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1080/15592324.2016.1261232</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">The other photoreceptor, Phytochrome C (PhyC), is proposed as the candidate gene for the Ma5 (SbPhyC) locus.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e14" source="CCA1" target="TOC1">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">Conserved circadian oscillator: morning-phased CCA1 binds EE elements in the TOC1 promoter and represses its transcription.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1186/1471-2229-12-32</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">LHY, CCA1, TOC1 (circadian oscillator).</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e15" source="TOC1" target="CCA1">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">Evening-phased TOC1 represses CCA1 transcription, completing the core oscillator feedback loop.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1186/1471-2229-12-32</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">LHY, CCA1, TOC1 (circadian oscillator).</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e16" source="LHY" target="TOC1">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">LHY and CCA1 act redundantly to repress TOC1 in the morning.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1186/1471-2229-12-32</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">LHY, CCA1, TOC1 (circadian oscillator).</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e17" source="CCA1" target="GI">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">Morning-phased CCA1/LHY represses GI to restrict GI expression to the afternoon/evening peak.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1186/1471-2229-12-32</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">GI (circadian regulator linking to CO→FT flowering pathway).</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e18" source="CCA1" target="PRR37">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">Morning-phased CCA1/LHY MYB TFs repress evening-phased genes including PRR37; canonical across Arabidopsis and grass oscillators. Conservation inferred for sorghum from the clock-gated bimodal SbPRR37 expression (Murphy 2011).</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1073/pnas.1106212108</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">circadian clock modulates SbPRR37 expression under...free-running conditions.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e19" source="ELF4" target="ELF3">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">ELF4 and LUX physically associate with ELF3 to form the Evening Complex; ELF3 serves as docking scaffold. Without ELF4/LUX, ELF3 loses repressive activity on clock output.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1038/nature10182</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">ELF3 served as a docking protein that brought together ELF4 and LUX; the biological activities of the three components peak in the evening, as does the formation of the evening complex.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e20" source="ELF3" target="PRR37">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">Evening Complex subunit ELF3 represses morning/evening PRR genes; inferred in sorghum from rice OsELF3-1 ortholog, which negatively regulates OsPRR1/37/73/95 (Zhao 2012).</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1371/journal.pone.0043705</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">OsELF3-1 negatively regulates OsPRR1, OsPRR37, OsPRR73 and OsPRR95 expression.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e21" source="ELF3" target="GHD7">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">Evening Complex subunit ELF3 represses Ghd7; in rice, OsELF3 suppresses Ghd7 expression, accelerating flowering under LD. Mechanism conserved in sorghum Evening Complex.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1371/journal.pone.0043705</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">OsELF3-1 suppresses a flowering repressor grain number, plant height and heading date 7 (Ghd7) to indirectly accelerate flowering under long-day (LD) conditions.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e22" source="LUX" target="PRR37">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">Evening Complex DNA-binding subunit LUX targets promoters of morning/evening PRR genes; rice OsLUX recruits OsELF3-1 and OsELF4s to repress Hd1 and Ghd7. Mechanism inferred for sorghum LUX ortholog.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1073/pnas.2122582119</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">The evening complex target suppresses the expression of Hd1 and Ghd7 directly to modulate photoperiodic flowering in rice.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e23" source="LUX" target="GHD7">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">LUX binds the Ghd7 promoter as part of the Evening Complex; rice evidence (OsLUX recruits ELF3/ELF4 to repress Ghd7).</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1073/pnas.2122582119</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">Evening complex target suppresses the expression of Hd1 and Ghd7 directly.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e24" source="GHD7" target="ELF3">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">SbGhd7 binds the SbELF3 promoter at the TGAATG motif and directly represses its transcription (Tadesse 2024 ChIP-seq + DAP-seq).</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1111/nph.19591</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">repressing transcription of...EARLY FLOWERING 3 (SbELF3).</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e25" source="GHD7" target="FKF1">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">SbGhd7 directly represses SbFKF1 (ChIP-seq target, TGAATG binding motif).</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1111/nph.19591</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">repressing transcription of...FLAVIN-BINDING, KELCH REPEAT, F-BOX1 (SbFKF1).</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e26" source="GI" target="PRR37">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">GI is required for normal diurnal SbPRR37 expression; sbgi-ems1 loses 2-5 fold PRR37 abundance across key time points.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1002/pld3.281</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">SbPRR37 transcript...levels in sbgi-ems1 plants were diminished by 2- to 5-fold at these time points.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e27" source="GI" target="CO">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">GI-FKF1 complex stabilizes CO and promotes CO transcription at 12 h after dawn, coincident with SbGI peak expression.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1002/pld3.281</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">The major effect of sbgi-ems1 was diminishment of SbCO transcript levels at 12 hr after dawn in either photoperiod.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e28" source="GI" target="EHD1">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">GI activates Ehd1 expression, mainly under SD at ZT12 (SD peak strongly attenuated in sbgi).</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1002/pld3.281</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">The peak of SbEHD1 occurring at 12 hr under SD was significantly reduced in sbgi-ems1.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e29" source="FKF1" target="CO">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">Blue-light-activated FKF1 forms a complex with GI that stabilizes CO protein and promotes CO transcription at late afternoon.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1186/1471-2229-14-148</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">In long days, GI activates CONSTANS (CO) expression in conjunction with FKF1.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e30" source="MA2_SMYD" target="PRR37">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">Ma2 locus (Sobic.002G302700, SMYD lysine methyltransferase) increases SbPRR37 expression amplitude in LD. Loss of Ma2 (ma2 = L141*) reduces PRR37 peak amplitude, advancing flowering.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1371/journal.pone.0212154</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">Ma2 delayed flowering in long days by selectively enhancing the expression of SbPRR37 (Ma1) and SbCO.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e31" source="MA2_SMYD" target="CO">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">Ma2 activates SbCO expression in LD; loss of Ma2 reduces both SbCO expression peaks.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1371/journal.pone.0212154</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">enhanced expression of both SbPRR37 (Ma1) and SbCO by Ma2 in Ma1Ma2 genotypes.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e32" source="ID1" target="CO">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">SbID1 establishes the capacity for SbCO expression; sbid1-2 mutants lose wildtype SbCO waveform across all time points.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.3389/fpls.2023.1304822</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">floral activator SbCO transcript accumulation in sbid1-2 was low at all time points and lacked the wild-type waveform.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e33" source="ID1" target="PRR37">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">SbID1 required for proper SbPRR37 diurnal expression; sbid1-2 abolishes PRR37 peaks.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.3389/fpls.2023.1304822</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">SbPRR37 and SbGhd7 transcripts were low at all time points in sbid1-2.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e34" source="ID1" target="GHD7">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">SbID1 required for proper SbGhd7 diurnal expression; primary Ghd7 peak at ZT16 is absent in sbid1-2.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.3389/fpls.2023.1304822</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">primary SbGhd7 peak at ZT16 in the wild type...did not occur in sbid1-2.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e35" source="ID1" target="EHD1">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">SbID1 (maize ID1 / rice Ehd2 ortholog) activates SbEhd1 expression. In rice, Ehd2 up-regulates Ehd1 under both SD and LD; ehd2 mutants show 145-365 day flowering delays.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1104/pp.108.125542</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">Ehd2 up-regulates the transcription of Ehd1 and of the downstream FT-like genes, Hd3a and RFT1, under both SD and LD conditions.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e36" source="ID1" target="FT8">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">SbID1 required for SbCN8/SbFT8 florigen expression peaks.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.3389/fpls.2023.1304822</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">Expression of florigen-encoding genes SbCN8 and SbCN12 was also lower in sbid1-2 than in the wild type.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e37" source="ID1" target="FT10">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">SbID1 required for SbCN12/SbFT10 florigen expression.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.3389/fpls.2023.1304822</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">Expression of florigen-encoding genes SbCN8 and SbCN12 was also lower in sbid1-2 than in the wild type.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e38" source="PRR37" target="CO">
      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">In LD, SbPRR37 upregulates SbCO expression at dawn (opposite to Arabidopsis). Differential SbCO expression between LD and SD requires PRR37. NOTE: this activation edge is paired with the PRR37-CO co-repressor action on SbCN8/12 (E025 below) — the net effect of PRR37 in LD is floral repression via the CO-Ehd1-FT axis.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1073/pnas.1106212108</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">SbPRR37 activates expression of the floral inhibitor CONSTANS and represses expression of the floral activators Early Heading Date 1, FLOWERING LOCUS T, Zea mays CENTRORADIALIS 8, and floral induction.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e39" source="PRR37" target="EHD1">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">SbPRR37 represses SbEhd1 expression in LD, preventing the induction of florigens.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1371/journal.pone.0105352</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">SbPRR37 and SbGHD7 repress expression of the grass specific floral activator, SbEHD1.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e40" source="PRR37" target="FT1">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">SbPRR37 suppresses SbFT1/SbCN15 florigen expression in LD via repression of SbEhd1 and/or direct repression in co-repressor complex with SbCO.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1111/nph.13834</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">cooperatively repressed by the classical sorghum maturity loci.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e41" source="PRR37" target="FT8">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
