      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">SbSOC1 (SbMADS31) activates LFY/AP1 in the shoot apical meristem, triggering floral meristem identity.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1111/tpj.70250</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">SbMADS31 (Sobic.004G003434) encodes a SOC1 MADS-box transcription factor subfamily protein.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e77" source="AP1" target="Flowering_Time">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">SbAP1 (SbMADS7) commits the meristem to floral identity and triggers flowering.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1111/tpj.70250</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">SbMADS7 (Sobic.002G010100)...act as regulators of floral initiation.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e78" source="GF14" target="Flowering_Time">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">Sb14-3-3 is a required scaffold of the florigen activation complex (binds all three florigens). Loss of 14-3-3 function breaks FAC assembly and delays flowering.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1080/15592324.2016.1261232</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">SbFT8 and SbFT10 directly interact with Sb14-3-3...florigen activation complex (FAC).</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e79" source="Gibberellin" target="Flowering_Time">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">Under inductive SD, early-morning peak of GA20/GA1 coincides with floral induction, hastening flowering. GA promotes flowering in grasses via DELLA destabilisation and FT activation.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1104/pp.104.2.347</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">under inductive 10-h photoperiods, the peak of GA20 and GA1 levels was shifted to an early morning peak, and flowering was hastened.</data>
    </edge>
    <edge id="e80" source="ID1" target="Flowering_Time">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">Direct integrative effect of SbID1 on flowering time via activation of SbCO, SbEhd1, SbFT8 (SbCN8), and SbFT10 (SbCN12). In the algebraic framework the three-florigen cascade is diluted by geometric-mean activation and rescued by bounded-inverse inhibition when PRR37/GHD7 co-drop; adding a direct short-cut edge captures the empirical 170-day flowering delay of sbid1-2 that is not faithfully transmitted through the multistep cascade. This is a modeling short-cut per REFINEMENT_AGENT Section 1.5 Step C, not a novel biological claim.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.3389/fpls.2023.1304822</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">sbid1-2 (Q199*) delays flowering ~170 days; SbCO transcript accumulation in sbid1-2 was low at all time points; SbCN8 and SbCN12 florigen transcripts reduced.</data>
    </edge>
